{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
my·tho·lo·gy
*IPA: /myθøløjɒ/
*AHD: /mĭthôlôjē/

===Etymology===
Greek - '''Μύθος''' (Mythos) [[story]] + '''λόγος''' (logos) [[telling]]<!--this needs development-->

===Noun===
'''mythology''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]''; ''plural'' '''mythologies''')

# (''countable'') The [[collection]] of [[myth]]s of a [[people]], [[concern]]ing their [[origin]], [[history]], [[deity|deities]], [[ancestor]]s and [[hero]]es.
# (''countable'') A [[similar]] [[body]] of myths concerning an [[event]], [[person]] or [[institution]].
# (''uncountable'') The [[systematic]] [[collection]] and [[study]] of myths.

